Beats today <a href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20250909373609/en/In-case-you-missed-it-Beats-introduces-a-collection-of-cases-for-the-latest-iPhone-models-in-three-stylish-and-practical-designs">announced</a> a new collection of cases for the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-17/">iPhone 17</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/iphone/">iPhone</a> Air, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-17-pro/">iPhone 17 Pro</a> and &zwnj;iPhone 17 Pro&zwnj; Max.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/09/iphone-17-beats-cases.jpg" alt="" width="2048" height="1152" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1018072" /><br/>
The Beats &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj; Case with <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/magsafe/">MagSafe</a> & Camera Control is designed to be thin and light. It is available for the &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj;, &zwnj;iPhone&zwnj; Air, &zwnj;iPhone 17 Pro&zwnj; and &zwnj;iPhone 17 Pro&zwnj; Max.<br/>
<br/>
The Beats &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj; Kickstand Case with &zwnj;MagSafe&zwnj; & Camera Control comes with a removable lanyard that doubles as a kickstand for hands-free landscape viewing. To form the kickstand, an adapter at the end of the lanyard slides open and attaches to a magnetic point on the side of the case. It is available for &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj;, &zwnj;iPhone 17 Pro&zwnj;, and &zwnj;iPhone 17 Pro&zwnj; Max.<br/>
<br/>
Both designs offer a double-shot hardshell case, an interior microfiber lining, and an outer matte finish that reduces scratches, smudges, and fingerprints. Both cases are available in Granite Gray, Bedrock Blue, Lime Stone, and Pebble Pink.<br/>
<br/>
The Beats &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj; Case with &zwnj;MagSafe&zwnj; & Camera Control is available for &#36;45, while the Beats &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj; Kickstand Case with &zwnj;MagSafe&zwnj; & Camera Control is available for &#36;59.<br/>
<br/>
In addition, the Beats &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj; Rugged Case with &zwnj;MagSafe&zwnj; & Camera Control provides extra protection. It features a rugged polymer backing with additional impact-absorbing sidewalls, an enclosed bottom for enhanced protection, and a grippy textured matte exterior.<br/>
<br/>
The Beats &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj; Rugged Case with &zwnj;MagSafe&zwnj; & Camera Control is available for &zwnj;iPhone 17&zwnj;, &zwnj;iPhone 17 Pro&zwnj;, and &zwnj;iPhone 17 Pro&zwnj; Max in Everest Black, Rocky Blue, Alpine Gray, and Sierra Orange for &#36;79. The new Beats cases are available to order starting today. <div class="linkback">Related Roundups: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-17/">iPhone 17</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-17-air/">iPhone 17 Air</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-17-pro/">iPhone 17 Pro</a></div><div class="linkback">Tag: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/beats/">Beats</a></div><div class="linkback">Related Forum: <a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/forums/iphone.99">iPhone</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/09/09/beats-announces-three-new-cases/">Beats Announces Three New iPhone Cases</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/beats-announces-three-new-iphone-cases.2465049/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>